===Noun===
{{en-noun|s|-}}

# A hardened block of [[mud]], [[clay]], etc, used for building.
#: ''This house is made of '''bricks'''''.
# {{uncountable}} Considered collectively, as a building material.
#: ''This house is made of '''brick'''''.
# {{basketball}} A shot which misses, particularly one which bounces directly out of the basket.
#: ''We can't win if we keep throwing up '''bricks''' from three-point land.''
# {{rfv-sense|Term of endearment, especially towards a subject who has performed a favour of an act of kindness without expectation of reciprocity.}}
#: ''Thanks for helping me wash the car. You're a '''brick'''.''
# {{slang}} An electronic device, especially a heavy box-shaped one, that has been rendered non-functional and, usually, non-repairable.
# {{informal}} a [[mobile phone]], especially one that is large and/or heavy relative to current models
# {{informal}} An external [[power supply]] consisting of a small box with an integral [[male]] [[power plug]] and an attached [[electric cord]] terminating in a power plug.  A [[power brick]].

